notes: Templates provide neutral slider baselines so phoneme customizer work can begin immediately.
Community contributors are encouraged to replace these placeholders with recordings and tuned parameters.
sources.source: Seeded placeholder templates for global language coverage

notes: Parameter sets approximate flagship voices from historical ETI Eloquence builds and high fidelity Loquendo ports.
Boolean toggles mimic how classic screen readers bundled abbreviation dictionaries and inline voice tags.
sources.source: Manual captures of heritage Eloquence releases for JAWS, Window-Eyes, and Loquendo SAPI-4

notes: Parameter sets derived from listening tests against the DataJake SAPI voice archives (eloq61.exe, IBM-ViaVoice_TTS-SAPI4.zip, SAPI5_IBMTTS.zip).
Templates aim to reproduce the smoother Studio variants and brighter ViaVoice timbres inside Eloquence's runtime so users can jump between NVDA and SAPI baselines.
Includes a capture of Code Factory's Eloquence for Windows SAPI 5 package so users can compare its voicing against the DataJake mirrors.
sources.source: Community SAPI-4 and SAPI-5 Eloquence/ViaVoice archives

notes: Templates approximate NV Speech Player presets using Eloquence slider ranges.
Extras record the original frame multipliers from nvSpeechPlayer so contributors can refine the mapping.
sources.source: NV Speech Player NVDA add-on voices

sources.notes: Imported from eSpeak NG variant voice definitions

emphasis.description: Boost or soften consonant attacks and vowel onsets to mirror how NV Speech Player emphasises foreground syllables.
emphasis.label: Emphasis shaping

gender.description: 0 = masculine tract target, 1 = feminine tract target.
gender.label: Gender resonance

headSize.description: Formant scaling comparable to vocal tract length.
headSize.label: Head size

headSizeContour.description: Simulates shorter or longer vocal tracts by biasing the first three formants, mirroring NV Speech Player's head size macro.
headSizeContour.label: Head size contour

inflection.description: Amount of pitch modulation between syllables.
inflection.label: Inflection

inflectionContour.description: Emphasises rising and falling transitions by shaping low-mid fundamentals and the 2–4 kHz glide band NV Speech Player uses for syllable inflection cues.
inflectionContour.label: Inflection contour

macroVolume.description: Blends pre-mix gain with broadband EQ so the voice can swell or sit back without clipping, echoing NV Speech Player's volume macros.
macroVolume.label: Macro volume envelope

nasalBalance.description: Controls nasal resonance cues so voices can favour open or pinched pronunciations without muting clarity.
nasalBalance.label: Nasal balance

overtones.description: Adds sparkle or dampens sibilants by shaping the 6–16 kHz band used by NV Speech Player's frication models.
overtones.label: Overtone brilliance

pitch.description: Primary pitch target controlling overall brightness.
pitch.label: Pitch

pitchHeight.description: Raises or lowers the perceived pitch centre by reshaping the fundamental energy band without affecting speaking rate.
pitchHeight.label: Pitch height

plosiveImpact.description: Accentuates consonant bursts (P, T, K, CH) by boosting the 1–4 kHz transient band where plosive energy peaks.
plosiveImpact.label: Plosive impact

rate.description: Base speed in words per minute mapped to Eloquence's internal range.
rate.label: Speaking rate

roughness.description: Noise component balancing rasp versus clarity.
roughness.label: Roughness

roughnessControl.description: Adds rasp or polishes brightness by boosting or cutting the 2.6–8.2 kHz band tied to NV Speech Player's roughness tables.
roughnessControl.label: Roughness

sampleRate.description: Output rate in Hertz after optional resampling.
sampleRate.label: Sample rate

scopeDepth.description: Controls how deep or shallow the voice feels by reshaping the upper-bass region present in NV Speech Player formants.
scopeDepth.label: Scope depth

sibilantClarity.description: Clarifies S/SH/CH/J style phonemes by shaping the 5–14 kHz sibilant noise band referenced by NV Speech Player.
sibilantClarity.label: Sibilant clarity

smoothness.description: Controls how much high frequency noise is removed to mimic NV Speech Player's aspiration blending.
smoothness.label: Smoothness

stress.description: Shapes the mid-high resonances that convey linguistic stress, mirroring NV Speech Player's intensity multipliers.
stress.label: Stress contour

subtones.description: Boost or trim the 60–400 Hz band that defines chest resonance and NV Speech Player's low frequency shaping.
subtones.label: Subtone weight

timbre.description: Balances lower formants against upper harmonics so the voice can sound darker or brighter without losing articulation.
timbre.label: Timbre focus

tone.description: Highlights the harmonic band responsible for tone colour, similar to NV Speech Player's cascade/parallel formant multipliers.
tone.label: Tone colour

toneSize.description: Simulates smaller or larger resonant cavities by biasing the first three formants—akin to NV Speech Player's head size macro.
toneSize.label: Tone size

vocalLayers.description: Controls the balance between fundamental energy and higher partials to simulate stacked voices or thinner single voices.
vocalLayers.label: Vocal layering

vocalRange.description: Expands or narrows the perceived vocal range by shaping both fundamentals and upper resonances.
vocalRange.label: Vocal range spread

volume.description: Output gain applied before NVDA's volume scaling.
volume.label: Volume

whisper.description: Introduces or removes aspiration-style whisper components across the band limited by NV Speech Player's breath tables.
whisper.label: Whisper blend
